<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-441-048  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 441 048.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  May 14 1990 n300 p34(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Trade revisions urged: possible boon to telecom exports. (to USSRand Eastern Europe)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Casatelli, Christine.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The US recommends a revised international trade policy to theCoordinating Committee for Multilateral Export Controls (COCOM).andO;The US plans to ease government regulation of the communicationsindustry regarding the export of certain telecommunicationsequipment to Eastern Europe and the Soviet Union.andP;  Restrictionsmay be lifted on such items as civilian packet switching systems,analog cellular systems, some low-level fiber optic equipment andtrunked radio telephone systems.andP;  Restrictions on exporting fasterfiber optic equipment and other more sophisticated communicationsequipment to the USSR remain and limit US companies' participationin a major installation of a 565Mbps fiber optic system there.andO;The permitted exports would enable Eastern Europe to build basiclocal and long-distance telephone systems.andP;  The changes becomeeffective at the end of 1990 if approved by COCOM at its Junemeeting.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Government RegulationInternational TradeCommunications IndustryCommunications EquipmentEastern EuropeSoviet UnionExportCoordinating Committee for Multilateral Export ControlsCommerce.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>